<paragraph id="8BD836E77445FFEBC4F9FBFCFB8F9B41" blockId="10.[166,1226,923,1408]" pageId="10" pageNumber="27">
Diagnosis. At first glance, 
<taxonomicName id="4C674D647445FFEBC653FBFCFD2A9A95" authorityName="Egger" authorityYear="1858" box="[600,761,1135,1161]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Criorhina" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="27" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pachymera">
<emphasis id="B913EAF57445FFEBC653FBFCFD2A9A95" box="[600,761,1135,1161]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="27">C. pachymera</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis id="B913EAF57445FFEBC703FBFCFC919A95" bold="true" box="[776,834,1135,1161]" pageId="10" pageNumber="27">male</emphasis>
looks like species of the genus 
<taxonomicName id="4C674D647445FFEBC4ADFB01FE229AB0" authority="Macquart, 1834" authorityName="Macquart" authorityYear="1834" box="[166,497,1170,1197]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Brachypalpus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="27" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B913EAF57445FFEBC4ADFB01FEE99AB0" box="[166,314,1170,1196]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="27">Brachypalpus</emphasis>
Macquart, 1834
</taxonomicName>
. Among European species of the genus 
<taxonomicName id="4C674D647445FFEBC7ADFB01FB7C9AB0" authority="Meigen, 1822" authorityName="Meigen" authorityYear="1822" box="[934,1199,1170,1196]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Criorhina" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="27" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B913EAF57445FFEBC7ADFB01FBC09AB0" box="[934,1043,1170,1196]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="27">Criorhina</emphasis>
Meigen, 1822
</taxonomicName>
, it is most similar to 
<taxonomicName id="4C674D647445FFEBC56DFB25FDB69ACC" authority="(Fallen, 1816)" baseAuthorityName="Fallen" baseAuthorityYear="1816" box="[358,613,1205,1232]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Criorhina" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="27" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="asilica">
<emphasis id="B913EAF57445FFEBC56DFB25FE1B9AD3" box="[358,456,1205,1232]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="27">C. asilica</emphasis>
(Fallén, 1816)
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="4C674D647445FFEBC666FB25FCBF9AD3" authority="Loew, 1871" authorityName="Loew" authorityYear="1871" box="[621,876,1205,1232]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Criorhina" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="27" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="brevipila">
<emphasis id="B913EAF57445FFEBC666FB25FD399AD3" box="[621,746,1205,1232]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="27">C.brevipila</emphasis>
Loew,1871
</taxonomicName>
, and 
<taxonomicName id="4C674D647445FFEBC7AFFB25FB169ACC" authority="(Meigen, 1822)" baseAuthorityName="Meigen" baseAuthorityYear="1822" box="[932,1221,1205,1232]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Criorhina" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="27" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="floccosa">
<emphasis id="B913EAF57445FFEBC7AFFB25FBC59AD3" box="[932,1046,1205,1232]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="27">C. floccosa</emphasis>
(Meigen, 1822)
</taxonomicName>
, all mimicking bees. 
<taxonomicName id="4C674D647445FFEBC584FB4BFDAE9AEE" authorityName="Egger" authorityYear="1858" box="[399,637,1240,1266]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Criorhina" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="27" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pachymera">
<emphasis id="B913EAF57445FFEBC584FB4BFDAE9AEE" box="[399,637,1240,1266]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="27">Criorhina pachymera</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
can be distinguished from 
<taxonomicName id="4C674D647445FFEBC7B7FB4AFBE79AEE" baseAuthorityName="Meigen" baseAuthorityYear="1822" box="[956,1076,1240,1267]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Criorhina" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="27" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="floccosa">
<emphasis id="B913EAF57445FFEBC7B7FB4AFBE79AEE" box="[956,1076,1240,1267]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="27">C. floccosa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by the hairy katepimeron (in 
<taxonomicName id="4C674D647445FFEBC56EFB6FFE089B09" baseAuthorityName="Meigen" baseAuthorityYear="1822" box="[357,475,1275,1302]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Criorhina" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="27" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="floccosa">
<emphasis id="B913EAF57445FFEBC56EFB6FFE089B09" box="[357,475,1275,1302]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="27">C. floccosa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, katepimeron is bare). 
<taxonomicName id="4C674D647445FFEBC6E9FB6FFCAF9B09" authorityName="Egger" authorityYear="1858" box="[738,892,1275,1302]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Criorhina" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="27" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pachymera">
<emphasis id="B913EAF57445FFEBC6E9FB6FFCAF9B09" box="[738,892,1275,1302]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="27">C. pachymera</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
clearly differs from 
<taxonomicName id="4C674D647445FFEBC068FB6FFB1A9B09" baseAuthorityName="Fallen" baseAuthorityYear="1816" box="[1123,1225,1275,1302]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Criorhina" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="27" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="asilica">
<emphasis id="B913EAF57445FFEBC068FB6FFB1A9B09" box="[1123,1225,1275,1302]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="27">C. asilica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="4C674D647445FFEBC4D2FA8CFE899B25" authorityName="Loew" authorityYear="1871" box="[217,346,1311,1337]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Criorhina" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="27" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="brevipila">
<emphasis id="B913EAF57445FFEBC4D2FA8CFE899B25" box="[217,346,1311,1337]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="27">C. brevipila</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by hind femur thickened, &lt;5× as long as their maximum width (
<figureCitation id="135C2A627445FFEBC045FA8CFB4B9B26" box="[1102,1176,1311,1338]" captionStart="Figs 43–46" captionStartId="10.[166,205,844,866]" captionTargetBox="[166,1224,174,824]" captionTargetId="figure-347@10.[166,1225,174,824]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="Figs 43–46. Criorhina pachymera male: 43 — habitus, dorsal view; 44 — habitus, lateral view; 45 — hind leg, lateral view; 46 — head, frontal view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6377559" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6377559/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="27">fig. 45</figureCitation>
) (in 
<taxonomicName id="4C674D647445FFEBC4ADFAD1FED99B40" baseAuthorityName="Fallen" baseAuthorityYear="1816" box="[166,266,1346,1372]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Criorhina" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="27" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="asilica">
<emphasis id="B913EAF57445FFEBC4ADFAD1FED99B40" box="[166,266,1346,1372]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="27">C. asilica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="4C674D647445FFEBC534FAD1FE6E9B40" authorityName="Loew" authorityYear="1871" box="[319,445,1346,1372]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Criorhina" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="27" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="brevipila">
<emphasis id="B913EAF57445FFEBC534FAD1FE6E9B40" box="[319,445,1346,1372]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="27">C. brevipila</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, hind femur slender,&gt; 6× as long as their maximum width).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BD836E77445FFEBC4F9FAF5FB6D9B9C" blockId="10.[166,1226,923,1408]" box="[242,1214,1381,1408]" pageId="10" pageNumber="27">
Note. Listed as a threatened species on the Balkan Peninsula by 
<bibRefCitation id="EFF64B167445FFEBC7E2FAF6FB689B9C" author="Vujic, A. &amp; Simic, S. &amp; Radenkovic, S." box="[1001,1211,1381,1408]" pageId="10" pageNumber="27" pagination="93 - 105" refId="ref7643" refString="Vujic, A., Simic, S. &amp; Radenkovic, S. 2001. Endangered species of hoverflies (Diptera, Syrphidae) on the Balkan peninsula. Acta entomologica Serbica, 5 (1 / 2), 93 - 105." type="journal article" year="2001">Vujić et al. (2001)</bibRefCitation>
.
</paragraph>
